 to generating facilities no larger than 20 MW. Order No. 2023, 184 FERC ¶ 61,054 at P 2.\n\n7Id. P 1.\n\n8 The filing parties that submitted the First Compliance Filing in Docket No. ER24-2009-000 also included the New England Power Pool (NEPOOL). Noting this difference, for simplicity this order refers to the filing parties in either proceeding as “Filing Parties.”\n\n9 Filing Parties also submitted a companion filing consisting of revisions not directly required by Order Nos. 2023 and 2023-A in Docket No. ER24-2007-000. The April Compliance Order addressed and accepted the proposed revisions submitted in Docket No. ER24-2007-000.\n\nDocket No. ER24-2009-001 - 3 accepted Filing Parties’ First Compliance Filing in part, effective August 12, 2024, and directed the Filing Parties to submit a further compliance filing within 60 days of the issuance of the April Compliance Order. Specifically, the Commission directed further revisions to ISO-NE’s Tariff to comply with the following requirements of Order Nos. 2023 and 2023-A: cluster study process, allocation of cluster network upgrade costs, site control, commercial readiness, LGIA deposit, transition process, elimination of reasonable efforts, affected system study process and modeling requirements, affected system pro forma agreements, and modeling and ride-through requirements for non-synchronous generating facilities. 10\n\nII. Second Compliance Filing\n\nFiling Parties state that through the Second Compliance Filing they propose revisions to ISO-NE Tariff section I.2.2, Tariff Schedules 11, 22 (ISO-NE LGIP), 23 (ISO-NE SGIP), and Tariff section III.13 in compliance with the April Compliance Order. Filing Parties also state that they have made conforming changes to the ISO-NE SGIP and Tariff Schedule 25 (Elective Transmission Upgrade Interconnection Procedures) 11 consistent with the directives of the April Compliance Order.\n\n10 April Compliance Order, 191 FERC ¶ 61,018 at PP 77, 85, 100, 102, 133, 135, 152-153, 